== Births == * [[Ōei]] 9th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1402]] {{ill|June 7|ja|6月7日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ichijō Kaneyoshi|ja|一条兼良|12=draft|12=draft}}, a waka poet (died [[1481]]). * [[Keichō]] 16th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1611]] {{ill|June 30|ja|6月30日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hoshina Masayoshi|ja|保科正之|12=draft|12=draft}}, the fourth son of {{ill|Tokugawa Hidetada|ja|徳川秀忠|12=draft|12=draft}} and lord of the Aizu Domain (died [[1673]]). * {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 15th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1730]] {{ill|June 21|ja|6月21日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Motoori Norinaga|ja|本居宣長|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Kokugaku scholar (died [[1801]]). * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1857]] {{ill|May 29|ja|5月29日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Itō Midaiharu|ja|伊東巳代治|12=draft|12=draft}}, a politician (died [[1934]]).
== Deaths == * [[260]] – {{ill|Cao Mao|ja|曹髦|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 4th Emperor of Wei during the Three Kingdoms period (born [[241]]). * {{ill|Enkyū|ja|延久|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1073]] {{ill|June 15|ja|6月15日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Emperor Go-Sanjō|ja|後三条天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 71st Emperor of Japan (born [[1034]]). * {{ill|Ōei|ja|応永|12=draft|12=draft}} 17th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1410]] {{ill|June 9|ja|6月9日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Shiba Yoshimasa|ja|斯波義将|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander and official of the Ashikaga Shogunate (born [[1350]]). * [[Genna]] 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} 1615, June 3) – {{ill|Sanada Yukimura|ja|真田信繁|12=draft|12=draft}} (also known as Yukimura, or "Kochi"), a military commander (born [[1567]]). * {{ill|Keian|ja|慶安|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1650]] {{ill|June 5|ja|6月5日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Tokugawa Yosinobu|ja|徳川義直|12=draft|12=draft}}, the ninth son of Tokugawa Ieyasu and the first lord of the Owari Domain (born [[1600]]).
