{{Not to be confused with|May 7|qq=May 7}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=五月初七|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 5월 7일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar May}} '''May 7''' is the 7th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taian|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Shōryaku|Shōkyō]] 2nd year / [[:en:Genkō (1331–1334)|Genkō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1333|1333]] [[:en:June 19|June 19]]) – The fall of the 【Rokuhara Tandai|六波羅探題】 in Kyoto occurred due to the attack by the forces of [[Ashikaga Takauji|足利尊氏]] who had turned against the bakufu. * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 10th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1582|1582]] [[:en:May 28|May 28]]) – During the campaign against the 【Mōri clan|毛利氏】, [[:en:Toyotomi Hideyoshi|Toyotomi Hideyoshi]] besieged the Ise province castle, {{ill|Takamatsu Castle (Binchū)|ja|備中高松城|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takamatsu Castle (Binchū)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 高松城 (備中国)}}, using a naval blockade. * [[:en:Yuanhe|Genna]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1615]] [[:en:June 3|June 3]]) – During the summer siege of Osaka (【Ōsaka Natsu no Jin】), the Tenshu of Ōsaka Castle burned down. * [[:en:Genroku|Genroku]] 16th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1703]] [[:en:June 20|June 20]]) – At Takemotoza in Osaka, the puppet theater play (【Joruri】) “[[:en:The Love Suicides at Sonezaki|Sonezaki Shinchū]]” by [[:en:Chikamatsu Monzaemon|Chikamatsu Monzaemon]] was first performed. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1872]] [[:en:June 12|June 12]]) – The first railway in Japan began provisional service between Shinagawa Station and Yokohama Station (currently [[:en:Sakuragichō Station|Sakuragichō Station]]).
== Births == * [[Ōei]] 9th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1402|1402]] [[:en:June 7|June 7]]) – [[:en:Ichijō Kaneyoshi|Ichijō Kaneyoshi]], a waka poet (died [[:en:1481|1481]]). * [[Keichō]] 16th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1611|1611]] [[:en:June 30|June 30]]) – [[:en:Hoshina Masayuki|Hoshina Masayoshi]], the fourth son of [[:en:Tokugawa Hidetada|Tokugawa Hidetada]] and lord of the Aizu Domain (died [[1673]]). * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 15th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1730]] [[:en:June 21|June 21]]) – [[:en:Motoori Norinaga|Motoori Norinaga]], a Kokugaku scholar (died [[1801]]). * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1857]] [[:en:May 29|May 29]]) – [[:en:Itō Miyoji|Itō Midaiharu]], a politician (died [[1934]]).
== Deaths == * [[260]] – [[:en:Cao Mao|Cao Mao]], the 4th Emperor of Wei during the Three Kingdoms period (born [[241]]). * [[:en:Enkyū|Enkyū]] 5th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1073|1073]] [[:en:June 15|June 15]]) – [[:en:Emperor Go-Sanjō|Emperor Go-Sanjō]], the 71st Emperor of Japan (born [[:en:1034|1034]]). * [[:en:Ōei|Ōei]] 17th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1410|1410]] [[:en:June 9|June 9]]) – [[:en:Shiba Yoshiyuki|Shiba Yoshimasa]], a military commander and official of the Ashikaga Shogunate (born [[:en:1350|1350]]). * [[Genna]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] 1615, June 3) – [[:en:Sanada Yukimura|Sanada Yukimura]] (also known as Yukimura, or "Kochi"), a military commander (born [[:en:1567|1567]]). * [[:en:Keian|Keian]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1650]] [[:en:June 5|June 5]]) – [[:en:Tokugawa Yoshinao|Tokugawa Yosinobu]], the ninth son of Tokugawa Ieyasu and the first lord of the Owari Domain (born [[:en:1600|1600]]).
