== Events == * [[:en:Shōryaku|Shōkyō]] 2nd year / [[:en:Genkō (1331–1334)|Genkō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1333|1333]] [[:en:June 19|June 19]]) – The fall of the 【Rokuhara Tandai|六波羅探題】 in Kyoto occurred due to the attack by the forces of [[Ashikaga Takauji|足利尊氏]] who had turned against the bakufu. * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 10th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1582|1582]] [[:en:May 28|May 28]]) – During the campaign against the 【Mōri clan|毛利氏】, [[:en:Toyotomi Hideyoshi|Toyotomi Hideyoshi]] besieged the Ise province castle, {{ill|Takamatsu Castle (Binchū)|ja|備中高松城|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takamatsu Castle (Binchū)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 高松城 (備中国)}}, using a naval blockade. * [[:en:Yuanhe|Genna]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1615|1615]] [[:en:June 3|June 3]]) – During the summer siege of Osaka (【Ōsaka Natsu no Jin】), the Tenshu of Ōsaka Castle burned down. * [[:en:Genroku|Genroku]] 16th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1703]] [[:en:June 20|June 20]]) – At Takemotoza in Osaka, the puppet theater play (【Joruri】) “[[:en:The Love Suicides at Sonezaki|Sonezaki Shinchū]]” by [[:en:Chikamatsu Monzaemon|Chikamatsu Monzaemon]] was first performed. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1872]] [[:en:June 12|June 12]]) – The first railway in Japan began provisional service between Shinagawa Station and Yokohama Station (currently [[:en:Sakuragichō Station|Sakuragichō Station]]).
== Births == * [[Ōei]] 9th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1402|1402]] [[:en:June 7|June 7]]) – [[:en:Ichijō Kaneyoshi|Ichijō Kaneyoshi]], a waka poet (died [[:en:1481|1481]]). * [[Keichō]] 16th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1611|1611]] [[:en:June 30|June 30]]) – [[:en:Hoshina Masayuki|Hoshina Masayoshi]], the fourth son of [[:en:Tokugawa Hidetada|Tokugawa Hidetada]] and lord of the Aizu Domain (died [[:en:1673|1673]]). * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 15th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1730]] [[:en:June 21|June 21]]) – [[:en:Motoori Norinaga|Motoori Norinaga]], a Kokugaku scholar (died [[1801]]). * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1857]] [[:en:May 29|May 29]]) – [[:en:Itō Miyoji|Itō Midaiharu]], a politician (died [[1934]]).
== Deaths == * [[260]] – [[:en:Cao Mao|Cao Mao]], the 4th Emperor of Wei during the Three Kingdoms period (born [[241]]). * [[:en:Enkyū|Enkyū]] 5th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1073|1073]] [[:en:June 15|June 15]]) – [[:en:Emperor Go-Sanjō|Emperor Go-Sanjō]], the 71st Emperor of Japan (born [[:en:1034|1034]]). * [[:en:Ōei|Ōei]] 17th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1410|1410]] [[:en:June 9|June 9]]) – [[:en:Shiba Yoshiyuki|Shiba Yoshimasa]], a military commander and official of the Ashikaga Shogunate (born [[:en:1350|1350]]). * [[Genna]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] 1615, June 3) – [[:en:Sanada Yukimura|Sanada Yukimura]] (also known as Yukimura, or "Kochi"), a military commander (born [[:en:1567|1567]]). * [[:en:Keian|Keian]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1650|1650]] [[:en:June 5|June 5]]) – [[:en:Tokugawa Yoshinao|Tokugawa Yosinobu]], the ninth son of Tokugawa Ieyasu and the first lord of the Owari Domain (born [[:en:1600|1600]]).
