== Births == * [[Ōei]] 9th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1402|1402]] [[:en:June 7|June 7]]) – [[:en:Ichijō Kaneyoshi|Ichijō Kaneyoshi]], a waka poet (died [[:en:1481|1481]]). * [[Keichō]] 16th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1611|1611]] [[:en:June 30|June 30]]) – [[:en:Hoshina Masayuki|Hoshina Masayoshi]], the fourth son of [[:en:Tokugawa Hidetada|Tokugawa Hidetada]] and lord of the Aizu Domain (died [[:en:1673|1673]]). * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 15th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1730|1730]] [[:en:June 21|June 21]]) – [[:en:Motoori Norinaga|Motoori Norinaga]], a Kokugaku scholar (died [[:en:1801|1801]]). * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1857|1857]] [[:en:May 29|May 29]]) – [[:en:Itō Miyoji|Itō Midaiharu]], a politician (died [[:en:1934|1934]]).
== Deaths == * [[260]] – [[:en:Cao Mao|Cao Mao]], the 4th Emperor of Wei during the Three Kingdoms period (born [[241]]). * [[:en:Enkyū|Enkyū]] 5th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1073|1073]] [[:en:June 15|June 15]]) – [[:en:Emperor Go-Sanjō|Emperor Go-Sanjō]], the 71st Emperor of Japan (born [[:en:1034|1034]]). * [[:en:Ōei|Ōei]] 17th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1410|1410]] [[:en:June 9|June 9]]) – [[:en:Shiba Yoshiyuki|Shiba Yoshimasa]], a military commander and official of the Ashikaga Shogunate (born [[:en:1350|1350]]). * [[Genna]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] 1615, June 3) – [[:en:Sanada Yukimura|Sanada Yukimura]] (also known as Yukimura, or "Kochi"), a military commander (born [[:en:1567|1567]]). * [[:en:Keian|Keian]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1650|1650]] [[:en:June 5|June 5]]) – [[:en:Tokugawa Yoshinao|Tokugawa Yosinobu]], the ninth son of Tokugawa Ieyasu and the first lord of the Owari Domain (born [[:en:1600|1600]]).
