{{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=五月初七|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 5월 7일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar May}} '''May 7''' is the 7th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Taian|qid=Q96759844|1=taian}}{{efn|ja|大安|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taian|1=taian|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q1306255}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Shōryaku|en|Shōryaku|qid=Q1324858|lt=Shōkyō|1=Shōryaku}} 2nd year / {{ill|Genkō (1331–1334)|en|Genkō (1331–1334)|qid=Q1194556|lt=Genkō|1=Genkō (1331–1334)}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1333|en|1333|qid=Q6004|lt=1333|1=1333}} {{ill|June 19|en|June 19|qid=Q2669|lt=June 19|1=June 19}}) – The fall of the 【Rokuhara Tandai|六波羅探題】 in Kyoto occurred due to the attack by the forces of {{ill|Ashikaga Takauji|en|Ashikaga Takauji|qid=Q297107|lt=足利尊氏|1=Ashikaga Takauji}} who had turned against the bakufu. * {{ill|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|en|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|qid=Q1145058|lt=Tenshō Era|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}} 10th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1582|en|1582|qid=Q6719|lt=1582|1=1582}} {{ill|May 28|en|May 28|qid=Q2588|lt=May 28|1=May 28}}) – During the campaign against the 【Mōri clan|毛利氏】, {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|en|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|qid=Q187550|lt=Toyotomi Hideyoshi|1=Toyotomi Hideyoshi}} besieged the Ise province castle, {{ill|Takamatsu Castle (Binchū)|ja|備中高松城|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takamatsu Castle (Binchū)|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 高松城 (備中国)|1=Takamatsu Castle (Bitchū)|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q1071073}}, using a naval blockade. * {{ill|Yuanhe|en|Yuanhe|qid=Q10889567|lt=Genna|1=Yuanhe}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1615|en|1615|qid=Q6784|lt=1615|1=1615}} {{ill|June 3|en|June 3|qid=Q2623|lt=June 3|1=June 3}}) – During the summer siege of Osaka (【Ōsaka Natsu no Jin】), the Tenshu of Ōsaka Castle burned down. * {{ill|Genroku|en|Genroku|qid=Q1325001|lt=Genroku|1=Genroku}} 16th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1703|en|1703|qid=Q6822|lt=1703|1=1703}} {{ill|June 20|en|June 20|qid=Q2666|lt=June 20|1=June 20}}) – At Takemotoza in Osaka, the puppet theater play (【Joruri】) “{{ill|The Love Suicides at Sonezaki|en|The Love Suicides at Sonezaki|qid=Q892262|lt=Sonezaki Shinchū|1=The Love Suicides at Sonezaki}}” by {{ill|Chikamatsu Monzaemon|en|Chikamatsu Monzaemon|qid=Q324986|lt=Chikamatsu Monzaemon|1=Chikamatsu Monzaemon}} was first performed. * {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|qid=Q3125096|lt=Meiji era|1=Meiji era}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1872|en|1872|qid=Q7753|lt=1872|1=1872}} {{ill|June 12|en|June 12|qid=Q2619|lt=June 12|1=June 12}}) – The first railway in Japan began provisional service between Shinagawa Station and Yokohama Station (currently {{ill|Sakuragichō Station|en|Sakuragichō Station|qid=Q801396|lt=Sakuragichō Station|1=Sakuragichō Station}}).
== Births == * {{ill|Ōei|en|Ōei|qid=Q1193078|lt=Ōei|1=Ōei}} 9th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1402|en|1402|qid=Q6113|lt=1402|1=1402}} {{ill|June 7|en|June 7|qid=Q2616|lt=June 7|1=June 7}}) – {{ill|Ichijō Kaneyoshi|en|Ichijō Kaneyoshi|qid=Q1656375|lt=Ichijō Kaneyoshi|1=Ichijō Kaneyoshi}}, a waka poet (died {{ill|1481|en|1481|qid=Q6631|lt=1481|1=1481}}). * {{ill|Keichō|en|Keichō|qid=Q1328185|lt=Keichō|1=Keichō}} 16th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1611|en|1611|qid=Q6768|lt=1611|1=1611}} {{ill|June 30|en|June 30|qid=Q2657|lt=June 30|1=June 30}}) – {{ill|Hoshina Masayuki|en|Hoshina Masayuki|qid=Q837236|lt=Hoshina Masayoshi|1=Hoshina Masayuki}}, the fourth son of {{ill|Tokugawa Hidetada|en|Tokugawa Hidetada|qid=Q314464|lt=Tokugawa Hidetada|1=Tokugawa Hidetada}} and lord of the Aizu Domain (died {{ill|1673|en|1673|qid=Q7617|lt=1673|1=1673}}). * {{ill|Kyōhō|en|Kyōhō|qid=Q1145048|lt=Kyōhō|1=Kyōhō}} 15th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1730|en|1730|qid=Q6957|lt=1730|1=1730}} {{ill|June 21|en|June 21|qid=Q2671|lt=June 21|1=June 21}}) – {{ill|Motoori Norinaga|en|Motoori Norinaga|qid=Q384647|lt=Motoori Norinaga|1=Motoori Norinaga}}, a Kokugaku scholar (died {{ill|1801|en|1801|qid=Q6877|lt=1801|1=1801}}). * {{ill|Ansei|en|Ansei|qid=Q1327259|lt=Ansei|1=Ansei}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1857|en|1857|qid=Q7680|lt=1857|1=1857}} {{ill|May 29|en|May 29|qid=Q2589|lt=May 29|1=May 29}}) – {{ill|Itō Miyoji|en|Itō Miyoji|qid=Q3156022|lt=Itō Midaiharu|1=Itō Miyoji}}, a politician (died {{ill|1934|en|1934|qid=Q18714|lt=1934|1=1934}}).
== Deaths == * {{ill|260|en|260|qid=Q30311|lt=260|1=260}} – {{ill|Cao Mao|en|Cao Mao|qid=Q550290|lt=Cao Mao|1=Cao Mao}}, the 4th Emperor of Wei during the Three Kingdoms period (born {{ill|241|en|241|qid=Q32065|lt=241|1=241}}). * {{ill|Enkyū|en|Enkyū|qid=Q1193638|lt=Enkyū|1=Enkyū}} 5th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1073|en|1073|qid=Q19437|lt=1073|1=1073}} {{ill|June 15|en|June 15|qid=Q2613|lt=June 15|1=June 15}}) – {{ill|Emperor Go-Sanjō|en|Emperor Go-Sanjō|qid=Q45844|lt=Emperor Go-Sanjō|1=Emperor Go-Sanjō}}, the 71st Emperor of Japan (born {{ill|1034|en|1034|qid=Q19324|lt=1034|1=1034}}). * {{ill|Ōei|en|Ōei|qid=Q1193078|lt=Ōei|1=Ōei}} 17th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1410|en|1410|qid=Q6151|lt=1410|1=1410}} {{ill|June 9|en|June 9|qid=Q2618|lt=June 9|1=June 9}}) – {{ill|Shiba Yoshiyuki|en|Shiba Yoshiyuki|qid=Q11500863|lt=Shiba Yoshimasa|1=Shiba Yoshiyuki}}, a military commander and official of the Ashikaga Shogunate (born {{ill|1350|en|1350|qid=Q6094|lt=1350|1=1350}}). * {{ill|Genna|en|Genna|qid=Q635245|lt=Genna|1=Genna}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} 1615, June 3) – {{ill|Sanada Yukimura|en|Sanada Yukimura|qid=Q3948081|lt=Sanada Yukimura|1=Sanada Yukimura}} (also known as Yukimura, or "Kochi"), a military commander (born {{ill|1567|en|1567|qid=Q6642|lt=1567|1=1567}}). * {{ill|Keian|en|Keian|qid=Q1146135|lt=Keian|1=Keian}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1650|en|1650|qid=Q6951|lt=1650|1=1650}} {{ill|June 5|en|June 5|qid=Q2622|lt=June 5|1=June 5}}) – {{ill|Tokugawa Yoshinao|en|Tokugawa Yoshinao|qid=Q1136186|lt=Tokugawa Yosinobu|1=Tokugawa Yoshinao}}, the ninth son of Tokugawa Ieyasu and the first lord of the Owari Domain (born {{ill|1600|en|1600|qid=Q6720|lt=1600|1=1600}}).
